---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout
  title="How Much Should a Logo Cost? | Logo Brief Guide"
  description="Understand what different budget ranges usually buy so you can avoid overpaying or underbuying on logo design."
  pathname="/how-much-should-a-logo-cost/"
>
  <section class="prose">
    <p class="eyebrow">Supporting page</p>
    <h1>How much should a logo cost?</h1>
    <p>
      The right budget depends on what you need. A simple starter logo is a
      different purchase than a full business identity system.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="soft-card">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Budget range</th>
            <th>What you can usually expect</th>
            <th>Main risk</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Very low budget</td>
            <td>Fast starter work, limited refinement, fewer deliverables.</td>
            <td>Generic results or missing source files.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Mid budget</td>
            <td>Better communication, more revisions, more tailored work.</td>
            <td>Still depends heavily on brief quality.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Higher budget</td>
            <td>More strategic thinking, better systems, broader deliverables.</td>
            <td>Overbuying if you only needed something simple.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section two-col">
    <div class="soft-card">
      <p class="eyebrow">Spend more when</p>
      <ul class="checklist">
        <li>The logo will be used everywhere</li>
        <li>You need a more distinctive identity</li>
        <li>You need multiple brand assets, not just one mark</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="soft-card">
      <p class="eyebrow">Spend less when</p>
      <ul class="checklist">
        <li>You are testing an idea</li>
        <li>You only need a basic starter brand</li>
        <li>You can live with a simpler design solution</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>
